{\*\cs39\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af9\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 } The most beneficial efficiencies are those associated with innovation{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s13{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af7\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af7\langfe255\hich\f7\fs20\lang1033\loch\f7\fs20\lang1033{\*\cs39\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 See comments of Professor Michael Porter who in commenting on the US Merger guidelines criticized them for its emphasis on static efficiencies and observed \'93Only scant attention is paid to innovation or progressiveness as an important goal that antitrust 
